The consultant should be familiar with project administration under ADB guidelines to support 
the  work  of  international  consultants,  and  should  have  experience  working  in  developing 
countries. Responsibilities will include:  
(i)  support the team leader, trade facilitation specialists, and resource persons in 
performing their assignments to implement the project; 
(ii)  support SERD staff in implementing the project; 
(iii)  provide  necessary  logistical  support  to  the  team  leader,  trade  facilitation 
specialists, and resource persons to perform their assignments to implement the 
project;  
(iv)  provide necessary logistical support to ADB missions;  
(v)  facilitate communication between consultants, government agencies, and ADB; 
and  
(vi)  participate in ADB missions as necessary.
